data.content:
Yes! MSTest v3.3+ supports **typed `DynamicData`** using tuples, eliminating the `object[]` boxing:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData<string, bool>(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string Input, bool Expected)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**Key changes:**
- `[DynamicData<string, bool>(...)]` — generic type args match the test parameters
- `IEnumerable<(string, bool)>` — tuples instead of `object[]`
- Compile-time type checking catches mismatches

Requires **MSTest.TestFramework 3.3+** and **Microsoft.Testing.Platform**. Supports up to 16 type parameters.
